          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Scaling and Monitoring for High Availability"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Deploy the API behind a reverse proxy like NGINX for SSL termination and rate limiting. Use horizontal pod autoscaling in Kubernetes based on CPU or custom metrics from Prometheus. Implement logging with structured formats (e.g., JSON) and integrate with tools like Grafana for real-time dashboards. Regularly audit API usage logs to identify bottlenecks and apply updates from the provider's changelog to maintain compatibility and security."
